Bardulis is called by Diodorus xvi 4 King of the Illyrians. He waged war with Perdiccas 111. of Macedonia and his younger brother Philip by whom he was defeated. Viriathus, the celebrated Lusitanian hero, a man of humble origin, who from a guerilla chieftain rose to be his country's champion against the Romans. His extraordinary successes against the enemy were obtained tae. 148-146. Gaius Laelius kept the field against him, but Gaius Plautius and after him Claudius Unimanus were vanq'uished ; Quintus Fabius Maximus Aemilianus was more successful. but, when his successor the praetor Quintius took the command, the Romans again suffered defeat after defeat, until Quintus Fabius Maximus Seruilianus, the adopted brother of Maximus Aemilianus (Β. c. 140), restored the fortune of war. But even after this success the Roman army was attacked while besieging Erisane and defeated by Viriathus, who, how- ever, contented himself, like the Samnite general at the Caudine pass, with concluding a peace with Aemilianus, in which he was acknowledged as the king of the Lusitanians. But Quintus Servilius Caepio, who had succeeded his brother in the command os Further Spain, renewed the war and shortly afterwards was base enough to procure the assassination of the Lusitanian hhero by bribing three of his confidants.
